Treasury Secretary James Baker saidhe expected the U.S. Trade deficit to fall by 15 billion to 20billion dlrs in 1987.    Commenting on the deficit during an interview on Cable NewsNetwork, Baker said "I think you're going to see a 15 to 20billion dlr reduction this year." The deficit was 170 billiondlrs in 1986.    Baker noted that the benefits of a weaker currency take 12to 18 months to affect the trade balance, and said it is now 18months since the Plaza agreement to lower the dollar's value. REUTER&#3;